conditional multiple point simulation with a texture synthesis algorithm presenting author julian m ortiz department of mini page 1 conditional multiple point simulation with a texture synthesis algorithm presenting author julian m ortiz department of mining engineering university of chile authors alvaro parra and julian m ortiz department of mining engineering university of chile abstract we present an algorithm based on texture synthesis that allows simulating a random field accounting for multiple point statistics and conditioning to hard data the algorithm proceeds by using a fixed search neighborhood and an ordered path to visit the nodes to be simulated in a lattice reproduction of multiple point statistics is ensured for patterns contained within the search neighborhood conditioning is achieved by combining this fixed neighborhood with a larger one that looks for hard data and modifies the conditional distribution if necessary the technique is illustrated with several examples and we discuss further avenues of research
